1. Acceptance

By installing, using, or exporting code from Shaders, you (“Licensee”) agree to be bound by this License Agreement (“Agreement”). If you do not agree, you must not use or deploy Shaders or any of its components.

2. License Grant

Subject to payment and compliance with this Agreement, Shader Effects grants you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, worldwide license to use, modify, and integrate Shaders components and exported code in your own projects, according to the license plan purchased.

Annual License: You may deploy any version of Shaders released during your active subscription term indefinitely, even after expiration, but you may not deploy or upgrade to newer versions until the license is renewed.

Lifetime License: You may deploy all versions of Shaders released during the lifetime of the company and while the npm registry continues to host the licensed packages. Shader Effects makes no guarantee of ongoing updates, support, or compatibility beyond reasonable efforts to maintain them.

Shaders is free to use in all environments, including production deployments and commercial projects. A Pro license unlocks additional features such as code export, Pro presets, priority support, and more.

3. License Tiers and Benefits

Free Tier: Shaders is free to use in all environments, including production deployments and commercial projects. Free users have access to the design editor, basic presets, and can install the npm package to use Shaders components in their projects.

Pro Tier: A Pro subscription unlocks the following benefits:

Code Export: Export clean, production-ready component code for Vue, React, Svelte, and other supported frameworks directly from the design editor.

Pro Presets: Access to an exclusive library of premium, hand-crafted presets not available to free users.

Discord Community Access: Receive a special role in the official Shaders Discord community with access to Pro-only channels.

Priority Support: Prioritized assistance with technical questions and implementation guidance. Support is limited to answering questions about Shaders usage and troubleshooting. Direct code implementation, extended consulting, and hands-on project work require a separate support contract and may be available upon request for an additional fee.

Pro benefits are tied to an active subscription. Upon expiration, access to Pro features (including code export and Pro presets) will be restricted, though previously exported code remains licensed per the terms in section 2.

4. Prohibited Uses

You may not:

Resell, sublicense, distribute, or repackage Shaders or its components as standalone items.

Use Shaders to create or power a competing tool, library, or service (including design editors, component libraries, visual-effect builders, or shader packs).

Redistribute Shaders presets (including modified versions of presets from the library) as downloadable files, preset libraries, or code packages. Using presets in your projects (including public websites and applications) is permitted; this restriction applies only to redistribution of the presets themselves.

Modify or remove any copyright, trademark, or attribution notice (including “Powered by Shaders” references) contained within the code.

Alter or circumvent license validation or metadata features.

Publish or share exported Shaders code or presets publicly as a library or downloadable package.

Use Shaders technology in SaaS products, design tools, or developer frameworks without a separate written OEM or partnership agreement with Shader Effects, Inc.

Official open-source projects may use Shaders without a license key only for their promotional or documentation websites, provided Shaders is not a core or monetized part of the project.

5. Telemetry and Privacy

Shaders may automatically collect and transmit limited, anonymous performance and usage data to Shader Effects' servers and third-party analytics services for the purposes of improving performance, reliability, and understanding how the library is used in production environments.

Data Collected:
- Performance metrics (frame rate, render times, component usage)
- Domain name where Shaders is deployed (e.g., "example.com", without URL paths)
- Browser family (e.g., Chrome, Firefox, Safari)
- Device type (mobile, tablet, or desktop)
- Renderer type (WebGPU or WebGL)

This data does not include personal information, IP addresses, user identifiers, or any data that can identify individual end users. Telemetry is sampled at a low rate (typically 1-5% of sessions) and respects Do Not Track browser settings.

Opt-Out:
You may disable telemetry collection entirely by setting the `disableTelemetry` prop on the Shader component or by configuring your environment to respect user privacy preferences. Even when enabled, telemetry will not collect data from users with Do Not Track enabled in their browser.

By using Shaders, you acknowledge and consent to this limited data collection solely for these operational purposes.

